                <div class="card border-0">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h5 class="card-title">What is Menstruation?</h5>
                        <p class="card-text">
                            <img src="/images/menstruation.png" style="width: 60px; height: auto" />
                            <br /><br>
                            A woman needs to understand what menstruation is, why it occurs,
                            and why it is significant. That, too, at the appropriate time,
                            namely before her first period.
                        </p>
                        <!-- Button trigger modal -->
                        <button type="button" class="btn " style="background-color: #ee3e5d; color: #ffffff;"
                            data-bs-toggle="modal" data-bs-target="#exampleModal">
                            Know More
                        </button>

                        <!-- Modal -->
                        <div class="modal fade" id="exampleModal" data-bs-backdrop="static" data-bs-keyboard="false"
                            tabindex="-1" aria-labelledby="staticBackdropLabel" aria-hidden="true">
                            <div class="modal-dialog modal-dialog-centered modal-dialog-scrollable">
                                <div class="modal-content">
                                    <div class="modal-header">
                                        <h5 class="modal-title" id="staticBackdropLabel">
                                            What is Menstruation?
                                        </h5>
                                        <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="modal"
                                            aria-label="Close"></button>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="modal-body">
                                        <p>Menstruation is also known as "period." A period is a time
                                            of 2 to 7 days during which a girl or woman's menstrual
                                            flow occurs, during which blood and tissue exit her body
                                            through her vagina.</p>


                                        <p>What causes this to happen? Each
                                            month, blood and tissue accumulate in the uterus in
                                            preparation for a fertilized egg in the case that a woman
                                            becomes pregnant. (The uterus is the location within a
                                            woman's body where a baby develops.) If the egg is not
                                            fertilized, the lining of the uterus exits the body via
                                            the vagina, and the girl or woman gets her period.</p>

                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="col-4">
                <div class="card border-0">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h5 class="card-title">Correct usage & disposal</h5>
                        <p class="card-text">
                            <img src="/images/waste.png" style="width: 60px; height: auto" />
                            <br /><br>
                            Today, municipal authorities and people are battling the massive amount of menstrual trash
                            that is being created. We urge people to adopt healthier disposal practices through
                            discourse.
                        </p>
                        <!-- Button trigger modal -->
                        <button type="button" class="btn  " style="background-color: #ee3e5d ;color: #ffffff;"
                            data-bs-toggle="modal" data-bs-target="#exampleModal1">
                            Know More
                        </button>

                        <!-- Modal -->
                        <div class="modal fade" id="exampleModal1" data-bs-backdrop="static" data-bs-keyboard="false"
                            tabindex="-1" aria-labelledby="staticBackdropLabel" aria-hidden="true">
                            <div class="modal-dialog modal-dialog-centered modal-dialog-scrollable">
                                <div class="modal-content">
                                    <div class="modal-header">
                                        <h5 class="modal-title" id="staticBackdropLabel">
                                            Correct usage & disposal
                                        </h5>
                                        <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="modal"
                                            aria-label="Close"></button>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="modal-body">
                                        <p>When you get your period, you'll need to use something to soak up the
                                            menstrual blood. There are lots of different products out there. It might
                                            take some experimenting to find what's right for you.
                                            Mostly used menstrual products are:
                                            pads (or sanitary napkins)
                                            tampons
                                            menstrual cups</p>


                                        <p>You can place used menstrual products inside a bag, seal them, and throw them
                                            in the trash. They will keep you from exposing another person to your bodily
                                            fluids. Period disposal bags also let you throw away a tampon at a friend's
                                            house without being embarrassed that they will see what's inside.</p>

                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="col-4">
                <div class="card border-0">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h5 class="card-title">Dealing with menstrual pain</h5>
                        <p class="card-text">
                            <img src="/images/pain.png" style="width: 60px; height: auto" />
                            <br /><br>
                            Women have menstrual discomfort regardless of geography or age. We can
                            practice tried-and-true Yoga poses to relieve menstruation discomfort.
                        </p>
                        <!-- Button trigger modal -->
                        <button type="button" class="btn" style="background-color: #ee3e5d ; color: #ffffff;"
                            data-bs-toggle="modal" data-bs-target="#exampleModal2">
                            Know More
                        </button>

                        <!-- Modal -->
                        <div class="modal fade" id="exampleModal2" data-bs-backdrop="static" data-bs-keyboard="false"
                            tabindex="-1" aria-labelledby="staticBackdropLabel" aria-hidden="true">
                            <div class="modal-dialog modal-dialog-centered modal-dialog-scrollable">
                                <div class="modal-content">
                                    <div class="modal-header">
                                        <h5 class="modal-title" id="staticBackdropLabel">
                                            Dealing with menstrual pain
                                        </h5>
                                        <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="modal"
                                            aria-label="Close"></button>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="modal-body">
                                        <p>It’s common to feel discomfort around your abdomen, lower back, and thighs
                                            when you’re menstruating.

                                            During your period, the muscles of your womb contract and relax to help shed
                                            built-up lining. Sometimes you’ll experience cramps, which means your
                                            muscles are at work. </p>


                                        <p>It sounds odd, but drinking water keeps your body from retaining water and
                                            helps to avoid painful bloating during menstruation. Warm or hot water is
                                            usually better for cramps, as hot liquids increase blood flow to your skin
                                            and may relax cramped muscles.
                                            Maintaining a healthy diet and keeping up a regular exercise regimen can go
                                            a long way toward preventing menstrual pain.
                                        </p>

                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>




